riorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4049.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Need opinions on haste item</span><hr size=1>   If you want a cheap, campable haste item, head to TT and do the hunter/forager cycle. There is a named spawn, Hangman, who drops a hangmans noose. It's less haste than a FBSS, but if has the advantage of being easy to camp. A single group can take him for sure, and probably just a partial group. <br><br> <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=288863>Fitemore Mystique</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uwubaogoldenarmz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wubao Goldenarmz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 176<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/1/02 10:37:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4049.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   easiest haste to get in the game ...</span><hr size=1> The easiest to obtain haste items in the game are:<br><br>1) If you're plane capable, the Haste Belts that drop off of mobs in Plane of Air. You spend enough time clearing even just the first island or two, and one's bound to drop. They always seem to drop for the wrong classes when we go up there, though, heh.<br><br>2) If you're not plane capable, then Hollowshade Moor. When the Grimling's have won the war. In the owlbear caves, there'll be a named Grimling Spawn. His RARE drop is a haste belt. Pretty easy to kill him for the belt. The pain is waiting on him to drop it (need patience for that) and getting the Grimlings to be the winners of the war (most people prefer owlbears to have won the war for the pelts ... and for some odd reason, the wolves keep winning the damn war on my server).<br><br>-Wu <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uealsurhelevorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ealsur Helevorn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/1/02 4:03:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4049.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: easiest haste to get in the game ...</span><hr size=1> I still dont have SoL, hope to get it soon though. I heard about the Haste belt from PoA from another thread, guess PoA is a bit easier than PoF, at least, the time I was in PoF was a real mess, I was in the break in group hehe <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>Thanks to everybody for their tips, I'll try my best to get one of the ones you mentioned <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><div align="center"> <img src="http://www.strike9.com/file.aspx/path=/Ealsur/fullsize/Ealsur.jpg"><br><b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=251429" target="_blank">Elven Berserk of 53 Dances</a></b><br><em>"The Power of Metal flowing in your veins... at the Speed of Light!"</em><br></div></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showPrevMessage?topicID=4049.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.sho